<!--
  Info.plist ADDITIONS for the LandTek iOS app.

  After `npx cap add ios`, the native project is at:
      mobile/ios/App/App/Info.plist

  Merge the keys below into that Info.plist (Xcode: right-click Info.plist ->
  Open As -> Source Code, and paste inside the top-level <dict>). These are the
  strings/permissions Apple reviewers and the runtime need.
-->

<!-- Why we schedule local notifications (shown in the iOS permission prompt).
     Required or the LocalNotifications permission request looks opaque. -->
<key>NSUserNotificationsUsageDescription</key>
<string>LandTek reminds you before your matter deadlines so you never miss a filing or hearing.</string>

<!-- Human-readable app name under the icon. -->
<key>CFBundleDisplayName</key>
<string>LandTek</string>

<!--
  App Transport Security: the app talks ONLY to the portal over HTTPS. We do NOT
  add any NSAllowsArbitraryLoads exception — cleartext stays blocked. leo.hayuma.org
  must present a valid TLS cert (it does, via nginx). No ATS additions needed;
  this block is here to document that the default (secure) posture is intentional.
-->
